Upload and Manage Content
=========================

Create a repository
-------------------

If you don't already have a repository, create one::

    $ http POST ${BASE_ADDR}/pulp/api/v3/repositories/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/ name=foo

Response::

    {
        ...
        "pulp_href": "/pulp/api/v3/repositories/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/9b19ceb7-11e1-4309-9f97-bcbab2ae38b6/",
        ...
    }


Upload a file to Pulp
---------------------

Each artifact in Pulp represents a file. They can be created during sync or created manually by uploading a file::

    $ http --form POST ${BASE_ADDR}/pulp/api/v3/artifacts/ file@./my_content

Response::

    {
        ...
        "pulp_href": "/pulp/api/v3/artifacts/6f847a21-a177-4a49-ad47-86f415b3830d/",
        ...
    }


Create content from an artifact
-------------------------------

Now that Pulp has the content, its time to make it into a unit of content::

    $ http POST ${BASE_ADDR}/pulp/api/v3/content/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/{{ plugin_dash_short }} artifact=${ARTIFACT_HREF} relative_path=my_content

Response::

    {}

Add content to a repository
---------------------------

Once there is a content unit, it can be added or removed::

    $ http POST ${BASE_ADDR}${REPO_HREF}modify/ add_content_units:="[\"http://localhost:24817/pulp/api/v3/content/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/{{ plugin_dash_short }}/ae016be0-0499-4547-881f-c56a1d0186a6/\"]"
